The paper deals with graph optimization problems, specifically the MEG (minimum equivalent graph) problem and the minimum SCSS (strongly connected spanning subgraph) problem. These problems are related to graph theory, algorithms, and optimization, which are all covered by various sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the problem of finding the minimum equivalent graph. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible categories as they deal with graph optimization problems. Finally, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a less likely category, but it is still possible as the paper discusses the time complexity of the algorithm.
